result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy T Keeler was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Carrying Concealed Weapon. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case recalled at 11:18. Same appearances. Pursuant to negotiations, and on motion of the State, Court amends charge to Carry Concealed Weapon pursuant to County Ordinance 63.015.  
Defendant enters a no contest plea  to the amended charge.  Court finds defendant guilty. Court ordered defendant pay a forfeiture of $100.00 inclusive of costs. Payable in SIX MONTHS or civil judgment.  Per the State's request, Court ordered defendant to relinquish their claim to the firearm and the defendant cannot petition for return of the firearm.
